hor/Liping Xie","line":92},{"title":"Author/Changbin Guo","target":"Author/Changbin Guo","line":93},{"title":"Author/Changbin Guo","target":"Author/Changbin Guo","line":94},{"title":"Author/Hongwei Liu","target":"Author/Hongwei Liu","line":95},{"title":"Author/Hongwei Liu","target":"Author/Hongwei Liu","line":96},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/zheng_concise_2020/zheng_concise_2020.pdf","line":98}],"metadata":{"id":"zheng_concise_2020","type":"article-journal","title":"A concise total synthesis and PPAR activation activity of hericerin from Hericium erinaceum","issued":{"date-parts":[[2020]]},"DOI":"10.1038/s41429-020-0303-8","container-title":"The Journal of Antibiotics","abstract":"Hericerin is an isoindolinone meroterpenoid alkaloid isolated from medicinal mushroom Hericium erinaceum with some bioactivities. Herein, a concise total synthesis of hericerin was described, with four steps and 30% overall yield starting from commercially available methyl 3-hydroxy-5-methoxybenzoate and geranyl bromide. A comprehensive effect of hericerin on HepG2 cell line was observed and confirmed by transcriptomic analysis. Furthermore, hericerin was found to be a new PPARγ agonist.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Zheng","given":"Zhongyong","literal":""},{"family":"Zheng","given":"Zhongyong","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Baosong","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Baosong","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Li","given":"Bao","literal":""},{"family":"Bao","given":"Li","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Zhengdi","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Zhengdi","literal":""},{"family":"Xie","given":"Liping","literal":""},{"family":"Xie","given":"Liping","literal":""},{"family":"Guo","given":"Changbin","literal":""},{"family":"Guo","give